  "title": "Cybersecurity Incident Response Manager, CISO Office",
  "description": "<p>As a <strong>Cybersecurity Incident Response Manager</strong> in our <strong>CISO office</strong>, you will lead incident response, threat intelligence, and use case development to protect the organisation from cyber threats. The ideal candidate will combine technical expertise in threat detection and incident management with strategic oversight, ensuring timely, effective, and compliant response to security incidents.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>What You'll Do:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Threat Monitoring &amp; Analysis</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Work closely with security monitoring and operations teams to strengthen detection and monitoring of cyber threats across the organisation.</li>\n  <li>Perform threat analysis and leverage intelligence to enhance detection, prevention, and response capabilities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Incident Response &amp; Management</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead response to cybersecurity incidents, overseeing investigations and executing containment, eradication, and recovery actions following established playbooks.</li>\n  <li>Develop, update, and maintain incident response playbooks, ensuring comprehensive documentation of actions, outcomes, and lessons learned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Collaboration &amp; Remediation</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Partner with internal teams (IT, network, application) to investigate, resolve, and prevent recurrence of security incidents.</li>\n  <li>Support vulnerability management initiatives and contribute to continuous improvement of security processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Training, Drills &amp; Reporting</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Participate in incident response drills and post-incident reviews, providing actionable insights to strengthen organisational resilience.</li>\n  <li>Review and act upon threat intelligence from internal and external sources, translating insights into preventative measures and reporting to leadership.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What You’ll Bring:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>5–10 years of experience in cybersecurity, with focus on threat management and incident response.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of incident management frameworks and best practices.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of AWS and Microsoft Azure environments preferred.</li>\n  <li>CISSP, AWS Cloud certifications advantageous.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with ability to work effectively across teams.</li>\n  <li>Highly motivated, detail-oriented, and committed to achieving positive security outcomes.</li>\n  <li>Degree in IT, Cybersecurity, Computer Science, or a related field.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
